<subsection xml:id="Question_2_1_3">
    <title> Problem 3</title>
    <p>
       The hint follows from question 1(a).

If <m>n</m> is even, let <m>n=2m</m>:

<md>
<mrow>t_1+t_2+\dots+t_n\amp= (t_1+t_2)+(t_3+t_4)+\dots+(t_{n-1}+t_n)</mrow>
<mrow>\amp=2^2+4^2+\dots+(2m)^2</mrow>
<mrow>\amp=2^2(1+2^2+3^2+\dots+m^2)</mrow>
<mrow>\amp=2^2\cdot \left(\frac{m(2m+1)(m+1)}{6}\right)</mrow>
<mrow>\amp=\frac{2m(2m+1)(2m+2)}{6}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp=\frac{n(n+1)(n+2)}{6}</mrow>
</md>

where we have used the result from section 1.1 concerning the sum of the first <m>n</m> squares. 

If <m>n</m> is odd:

<md>
<mrow>t_1+t_2+\dots+t_n\amp= (t_1+t_2)+(t_3+t_4)+\dots+(t_{n-2}+t_{n-1})+t_n</mrow>
<mrow>\amp=\frac{(n-1)(n)(n+1)}{6}+\frac{n(n+1)}{2}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp=\frac{(n-1)(n)(n+1)+3n(n+1)}{6}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp=\frac{(n+1)(n^2-n+3n)}{6}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp=\frac{(n+1)(n)(n+2)}{6}</mrow>
</md>
    </p>
</subsection>

